-- Infineon up on talk of interest from Samsung, Intel
-- 
-- Tue May 6, 2008 8:53am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/06/us-infineon-intel-idUSWEB404920080506

 

 FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - Shares in Infineon ( IFXGn.DE ) rose more than 7 percent on Tuesday as traders cited market talk that Samsung Electronics ( 005930.KS ) and Intel ( INTC.O ) could be interested in the German chipmaker. 

 "The rumor is that they (Samsung and Intel) would bid more than 10 euros," one trader said. Other traders in London and Paris also heard the rumor. Infineon declined to comment. A spokeswoman for Samsung Electronics had no comment on the rumor. Infineon shares were up 3.8 percent at 6.56 euros by 1245 GMT, while Germany's DAX index  .GDAXI  was down 0.8 percent. (Reporting by  Eva Kuehnen , Kirsti Knolle and Stefan Schaaf in Frankfurt,  Amanda Cooper  in London, Juliette Rouillon in Paris and So-eui Rhee in Seoul; Editing by Quentin Bryar)